This folder contains all R scripts used to simulate, process, and visualise gene drive scenarios for the one locus MEREA system.

The directory is structured to separate gene drive configurations (e.g. bisex vs two-locus) and script functionality (e.g. simulation vs plotting vs data preparation).

üìÅ Subdirectories:
  
- bisex/
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_actual_frequency.R   : Runs simulations for idealised (mathematically simplified) bisex gene drive scenarios
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_realistic_frequency.R: Runs simulations under ecologically realistic assumptions
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_no_release.R         : Models population dynamics without any gene drive release
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_male_release.R       : Models male-only bisex drive releases under realistic conditions

- plots/
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_releases_all.R       : Compares population dynamics across different release schedules
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_thresholds_all.R     : Visualises suppression success vs introduction threshold
    ‚Ü≥ bisex_pure.R               : Visualises mathematically ideal scenario (single release) across all thresholds

- dataframe/
    ‚Ü≥ realistic_bisex_combined.R : Prepares and combines realistic simulation outputs into a unified data frame
    ‚Ü≥ actual_bisex_combined.R    : Prepares combined output for idealised bisex scenarios